f=Engineering/mia/operational/tool/mia-tool-requirements.md · p=What mia needs, what happens without each. external tool call plan-locked (Rail sandboxed (Rail 2); mia runs data changes (Rail 3). · h2:Requirements=\| Need \| Tool / access \| Used by \| Without it \| · h2:Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Requirements=\| Repo read/write for frontend code \| repo scope (per stack-profile) \| all skills \| Core; without write, design-only \| · h2:Requirements=\| Frontend framework + build \| per stack-profile \| all skills \| Method-only guidance \| · h2:Requirements=\| Brand kit access \| atlas's kit (Brand Studio) \| design-tokens \| Provisional tokens, labeled; atlas is pending source of truth \| · h2:Requirements=\| Token tooling \| Style Dictionary / CSS vars (per stack-profile) \| design-tokens \| Manual token management, labeled \| · h2:Requirements=\| Agentation MCP \| agentation.com (proposed connector, §5) \| frontend-verification \| Feedback from description, labeled less precise \| · h2:Requirements=\| Browser verification \| quinn's Reticle + Playwright \| frontend-verification \| Manual checklist; E-tier UNMET \| · h2:Requirements=\| Perf tooling \| Lighthouse-class (per stack-profile) \| frontend-performance \| Emulated throttling, labeled fidelity gap \| · h2:Explicit non-needs (by design)=**No data change execution** mia builds UI; data changes dana operator (Rail 3)., **No production deploy control** ops ships; mia's code passes quinn's gate first., **No secrets client code** anything frontend bundle public (aegis's concern). · n=mia primary builder genuine code write access change passes dev's review (incl. integrity checks: mock data, hardcoded brand values), quinn's gate, aegis client-security surfaces., Agentation Reticle/Playwright proposed connectors (plan §5), surfaced operator deployment; skills degrade method/manual without them. · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| Tool \| Source \| Purpose \| Always-on \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\|------\|--------\|---------\|-----------\| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Browserbase MCP** \| [docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp](https://docs.browserbase.com/integrations/mcp) \| Cloud browser automation: cross-browser UI testing, visual regression via screenshots, mobile viewport verification. 6 tools: start, navigate, act, observe, extract, end. \| ⚠️ On-demand — activate during QA/verification phases \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Website Cloner** \| [github.com/horuz-ai/claude-plugins](https://github.com/horuz-ai/claude-plugins) (website-cloner SKILL) \| 4-agent pipeline cloning sites into React+Tailwind: screenshotter → extractor → cloner → QA reviewer. Competitive design analysis, rapid prototyping from reference sites. \| ❌ No — expensive multi-agent pipeline; use /clone-website explicitly \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **awesome-design-md** \| [github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md](https://github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md) — MIT \| 70+ brand DESIGN.md files (Apple, Stripe, Linear, Vercel, Nike, etc.). Drop into project → AI agents generate brand-consistent UI. Bridges with Brand Studio/atlas design tokens. \| ⚠️ Reference — pull DESIGN.md when building UI, not a runtime tool \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=See Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md setup instructions full tool catalog.